benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to payment

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04 cover successful modifications with various header and body conditions.
Empty Response: @TC04 covers removal of custom fields via empty array.
Non-Existing Resource: @TC06 covers paymentId not found scenario.
Invalid paymentId format: @TC05 covers invalid UUID format.
Missing required header: @TC07 tests missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy.
Malformed JSON body: @TC09 tests invalid JSON payloads.
Invalid CustomField objects: @TC10 covers validation errors for bad data.
Unauthorized access: @TC11 tests missing/invalid auth token.
Server error: @TC12 simulates database or system failures.
Injection attempt: @TC13 tests security against SQL injection.
Large payloads: @TC14 and @TC15 test large number of custom fields and max length values.
Extra parameters: @TC16 tests handling of unexpected properties.
Data consistency: @TC17 verifies subsequent GET reflects updates.
Duplicate custom field names: @TC18 tests handling of duplicates.
Performance: @TC19 and @TC20 cover concurrent requests and large payloads.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No specific tests for role-based access control beyond missing header scenario.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to test throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios check for ETag, Cache-Control headers, or caching mechanisms.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large datasets with page tokens or limits.
Include tests for role-based authorization to ensure only permitted users can modify custom fields.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volumes.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
